----- Questions


NodeJS is a JS runtime built on google's V8 JS engine.

The V8 is the one who will parse and execute the code.

----- Why and when to use NodeJS

-- NodeJS Pros

Single threaded on event driven, non-blocking I/O model.

Perfect for building fast and scalable data intensive apps.

-- Use NodeJS

API with database behind it (preferably NoSQL)
Data streaming (Example: Youtube)
Real-time chat application
Server-side web application

-- Don't use NodeJS

Apps with heavy server-side processing(CPU-intensive)